---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="New Video: Jenny Lynn from Basin & Grange - Molinello Music" description="Basin & Grange release a music video for Jenny Lynn, a cover from their debut album Walk You Down the Road.">
  <article class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <p class="text-brand-orange font-heading font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">June 3, 2024 &middot; Highland, Utah</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-4">New Video:</h1>
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-600 mb-10">"Jenny Lynn" from Basin & Grange</h2>

      <!-- Video -->
      <div class="aspect-video rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg mb-10">
        <iframe
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/aIYESv3ZPEw"
          title="Basin & Grange - Jenny Lynn music video"
          class="w-full h-full"
          frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
          allowfullscreen
        ></iframe>
      </div>

      <!-- Article body -->
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Utah-based bluegrass band <strong>Basin & Grange</strong> releases their debut album, <em>Walk You Down the Road</em>, today. Packed with the band's renowned harmonies, it includes ten original songs and two favorite cover songs. One of those covers is "Jenny Lynn", written by the late <strong>Ron Spears</strong>. Ron, a Utah native, was a recent member of <strong>Fast Track</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://lnkfi.re/bng-walkalbum" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-block bg-brand-orange text-white font-heading font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-orange-600 transition-colors text-base">
            Listen to Walk You Down the Road
          </a>
        </p>
        <p>
          The first track, "Pines of Caroline", written by band member Boyd Timothy, was featured in the <strong>2021 IBMA Songwriter Showcase</strong>. "Bad Day at Sheep Creek", the album's featured single, depicts the unfortunate tragedy of a young Utah family who lost their lives to a sudden intense flash flood in 1965.
        </p>

        <!-- Quotes -->
        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-brand-orange pl-6 italic text-gray-600">
          <p class="mb-2">"Walk You Down the Road is more than just an album&mdash;it's a heartfelt testament to the power of music and camaraderie."</p>
          <cite class="not-italic font-heading font-bold text-brand-dark text-base">&mdash; Josh Stewart, banjo</cite>
        </blockquote>

        <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-brand-orange pl-6 italic text-gray-600">
          <p class="mb-2">"Each track is a window into our shared journey, reflecting the landscapes and lives that have inspired us."</p>
          <cite class="not-italic font-heading font-bold text-brand-dark text-base">&mdash; Josh Stewart</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- Album credits -->
      <div class="mt-12 bg-brand-warm rounded-xl p-8">
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl mb-6">Album Credits</h3>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-heading font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Producer</p>
            <p class="text-brand-dark">Boyd Timothy</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 font-heading font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-1">Mixing & Mastering</p>
            <p class="text-brand-dark">Scott Vestal</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h4 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-4">Musicians</h4>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
            <span class="font-heading font-semibold">Bill Moore</span>
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">mandolin, upright bass, vocals</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
            <span class="font-heading font-semibold">Mark Smith</span>
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">dobro, upright bass, vocals</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
            <span class="font-heading font-semibold">Jonah Schupbach</span>
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">guitar, vocals</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
            <span class="font-heading font-semibold">Josh Stewart</span>
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">banjo, guitar, vocals</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-gray-200 pb-2">
            <span class="font-heading font-semibold">Boyd Timothy</span>
            <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">guitar, mandolin, upright bass, vocals</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- About the band -->
      <div class="mt-12 space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl">About Basin & Grange</h3>
        <p>
          Basin & Grange is a five-piece all-acoustic bluegrass band with roots in Salt Lake City, Utah. After winning the inaugural band competition at the <strong>Durango Meltdown Bluegrass Festival</strong> in 2022, they were invited back as a main stage performer in 2023. Best known for their bluegrass harmony singing, the band plays regularly in the Intermountain West.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Social -->
      <div class="mt-12 bg-brand-charcoal text-white rounded-xl p-8">
        <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-lg mb-4">Visit Basin & Grange on Social Media</h3>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <a href="https://www.facebook.com/basingrange" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors" aria-label="Facebook">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M24 12.073c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12s-12 5.373-12 12c0 5.99 4.388 10.954 10.125 11.854v-8.385H7.078v-3.47h3.047V9.43c0-3.007 1.792-4.669 4.533-4.669 1.312 0 2.686.235 2.686.235v2.953H15.83c-1.491 0-1.956.925-1.956 1.874v2.25h3.328l-.532 3.47h-2.796v8.385C19.612 23.027 24 18.062 24 12.073z"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.instagram.com/basinandgrange/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors" aria-label="Instagram">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2.163c3.204 0 3.584.012 4.85.07 3.252.148 4.771 1.691 4.919 4.919.058 1.265.069 1.645.069 4.849 0 3.205-.012 3.584-.069 4.849-.149 3.225-1.664 4.771-4.919 4.919-1.266.058-1.644.07-4.85.07-3.204 0-3.584-.012-4.849-.07-3.26-.149-4.771-1.699-4.919-4.92-.058-1.265-.07-1.644-.07-4.849 0-3.204.013-3.583.07-4.849.149-3.227 1.664-4.771 4.919-4.919 1.266-.057 1.645-.069 4.849-.069zM12 0C8.741 0 8.333.014 7.053.072 2.695.272.273 2.69.073 7.052.014 8.333 0 8.741 0 12c0 3.259.014 3.668.072 4.948.2 4.358 2.618 6.78 6.98 6.98C8.333 23.986 8.741 24 12 24c3.259 0 3.668-.014 4.948-.072 4.354-.2 6.782-2.618 6.979-6.98.059-1.28.073-1.689.073-4.948 0-3.259-.014-3.667-.072-4.947-.196-4.354-2.617-6.78-6.979-6.98C15.668.014 15.259 0 12 0zm0 5.838a6.162 6.162 0 100 12.324 6.162 6.162 0 000-12.324zM12 16a4 4 0 110-8 4 4 0 010 8zm6.406-11.845a1.44 1.44 0 100 2.881 1.44 1.44 0 000-2.881z"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@basinandgrange" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors" aria-label="YouTube">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M23.498 6.186a3.016 3.016 0 00-2.122-2.136C19.505 3.545 12 3.545 12 3.545s-7.505 0-9.377.505A3.017 3.017 0 00.502 6.186C0 8.07 0 12 0 12s0 3.93.502 5.814a3.016 3.016 0 002.122 2.136c1.871.505 9.376.505 9.376.505s7.505 0 9.377-.505a3.015 3.015 0 002.122-2.136C24 15.93 24 12 24 12s0-3.93-.502-5.814zM9.545 15.568V8.432L15.818 12l-6.273 3.568z"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
